"{\"uid\": \"wcjb.com-2024-07-01-leanne-wong-selected-replacement-athlete-us-olympic-team\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"MINNEAPOLIS, Minn.  - Gator gymnastics standout, Leanne Wong, has been selected as a replacement athlete for the 2024 U.S.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 11, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minneapolis\", \"score\": 0.9999999900944658, \"rank\": 9.905505090095249e-09, \"text\": \"MINNEAPOLIS\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minneapolis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minneapolis\"}, {\"begin\": 49, \"end\": 55, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leanne_Battersby\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Leanne\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leanne_Battersby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leanne_Battersby\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gymnastics Olympic Team, marking her second Olympic berth after serving as a replacement athlete for the U.S. Tokyo team in 2020.\", \"from\": 123, \"to\": 252, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 123, \"end\": 133, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artistic_gymnastics\", \"score\": 0.9918284925912835, \"rank\": 0.00525053295535241, \"text\": \"Gymnastics\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artistic_gymnastics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artistic_gymnastics\"}, {\"begin\": 233, \"end\": 238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9917491800500203, \"rank\": 0.008149658730360474, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Sunday, Leanne Wong enhanced her scores from Day 1 in vault, balance beam, and floor exercise, narrowly missing her previous uneven bars mark by just 0.025 points.\", \"from\": 254, \"to\": 420, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 265, \"end\": 271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leanne_Battersby\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Leanne\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leanne_Battersby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leanne_Battersby\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She started the evening strongly with a flawless performance on the uneven bars.\", \"from\": 422, \"to\": 502, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Wong made significant score improvements on both the balance beam and floor exercise events.\", \"from\": 503, \"to\": 595, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She minimized deductions on the beam and avoided stepping out of bounds, which contributed to her strong floor score on Sunday.\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 723, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Wong concluded her competition with a solid landing on her Cheng vault, earning the third-highest vault score of the evening at 14.50.\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 858, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The final night of the trials did not disappoint.\", \"from\": 860, \"to\": 909, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The competition was unmatched.\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 940, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It comes to no surprise that, Simone Biles, who secured the all-around champion title at the trials, earned an automatic spot on the U.S. roster.\", \"from\": 941, \"to\": 1086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 971, \"end\": 983, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The selection of the remaining four competing team members and replacement athletes, including Wong, was made by a committee.\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1212, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team USA's roster includes:  Simone Biles  Sunisa Lee  Jordan Chiles  Jade Carey  Hezley Rivera  Leanne Wong (replacement athlete, travel)  Joscelyn Roberson (replacement athlete, travel)  Wong will travel to Paris in her role as a replacement athlete, ready to step in if needed to support Team USA in their pursuit of Olympic glory.\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1548, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1214, \"end\": 1222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9995248148893011, \"rank\": 0.0004713648099129708, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1243, \"end\": 1255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}, {\"begin\": 1257, \"end\": 1267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sunisa Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 1269, \"end\": 1282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Chiles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\"}, {\"begin\": 1284, \"end\": 1294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Carey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jade Carey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Carey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jade_Carey\"}, {\